  "title": "The Capital's Underworld: Essence of a Politician",
  "summary": "On a New Alderaan street, the soldier Rasi, fresh from an entertainment shop, crosses paths with the dozing Horansi Ambassador K'tyyri, the irritable errand-running medic Myiari, and Senator Tokoga of Dac, who travels under the watch of a stoic bodyguard. Their casual conversation drifts from Myiari's grumbling about her brothers to the stalled Incorporation of Organized Crime Act, which only Dac among the founding worlds supports, the Core Worlds viewing it as a libertarian overreach. The talk turns philosophical as Rasi questions why Tokoga refuses to act the part of a celebrated politician, and the Senator explains that on Dac politics is treated as a scholarly profession judged by ideas rather than image. They also note that the crime lord Bavon Nass has gone quiet since his foiled plot, though none believe he is finished. The gathering breaks up amiably as each returns to their errands and duties.",
